				<header class="page-header">
					<h1 class="page-title">
													Daily Archives: <span>November 7, 2014</span>											</h1>
				</header>

				
								
					
	<article id="post-3223" class="post-3223 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-korea-north category-media">
		<header class="entry-header">
						<h1 class="entry-title"><a href="https://asiansecurityblog.wordpress.com/2014/11/07/my-national-interest-essay-on-the-ridiculous-media-hysteria-over-kim-jong-uns-disappearance/" rel="bookmark">My National Interest Essay on the Ridiculous Media Hysteria over Kim Jong Un&rsquo;s&nbsp;Disappearance</a></h1>
			
						<div class="entry-meta">
				<span class="sep">Posted on </span><a href="https://asiansecurityblog.wordpress.com/2014/11/07/my-national-interest-essay-on-the-ridiculous-media-hysteria-over-kim-jong-uns-disappearance/" title="3:15 pm" rel="bookmark"><time class="entry-date" datetime="2014-11-07T15:15:13+09:00">November 7, 2014</time></a><span class="by-author"> <span class="sep"> by </span> <span class="author vcard"><a class="url fn n" href="https://asiansecurityblog.wordpress.com/author/asiansecurityblog/" title="View all posts by Robert E Kelly" rel="author">Robert E Kelly</a></span></span>			</div><!-- .entry-meta -->
			
						<div class="comments-link">
				<a href="https://asiansecurityblog.wordpress.com/2014/11/07/my-national-interest-essay-on-the-ridiculous-media-hysteria-over-kim-jong-uns-disappearance/#comments">10</a>			</div>
					</header><!-- .entry-header -->

				<div class="entry-content">
			<div class="cs-rating pd-rating" id="pd_rating_holder_478481_post_3223"></div><br/><p align="justify"><a href="https://asiansecurityblog.files.wordpress.com/2014/11/untitled.png"><img title="untitled" style="border-top:0;border-right:0;background-image:none;border-bottom:0;float:left;padding-top:0;padding-left:0;border-left:0;display:inline;padding-right:0;" border="0" alt="untitled" src="https://asiansecurityblog.files.wordpress.com/2014/11/untitled_thumb.png?w=321&#038;h=321" width="321" align="left" height="321"/></a></p>
<p align="justify">Admit it,&nbsp; you miss the wild speculation about Kim Jong Un’s disappearance last month. It was lunatic fun, right? <strong>Was he dead? <em>Was his sister in charge?</em> WAS HE REPLACED BY ALIENS?!!</strong> Run for the hills! </p>
<p align="justify">To me, in retrospect, the <strong>big story was not KJU’s disappearance, but the wild, almost lunatic conspiracy-theorizing it unleashed in the West.</strong> </p>
<p align="justify">North Korea is a running punch-line in the West. Kim Jong Il was the villain in <em>Team America</em>. The story that the Norks found a unicorn a few years ago got play for weeks in the US for its sheer laugh value. So this essay was an effort to get a handle on this – why do Western media feel license to make any wild, preposterous claim they want about North Korea? Where does this bizarre obsession come from? There’s probably a good MA thesis in here actually if you were serious about it. </p>
<p align="justify">The following essay was first published by the <a href="http://www.lowyinterpreter.org/post/2014/10/30/What-did-we-learn-from-all-the-Kim-Jong-Un-has-dissappeared-hysteria.aspx?COLLCC=2212766809&amp;">Lowy Institute</a>, and then <a href="http://nationalinterest.org/blog/the-buzz/north-korea-the-mafia-lessons-the-kim-jong-un-has-11584">picked up by The National Interest</a><em></em>. This was the first time I was published by <em>TNI</em>, so that was pretty cool. My thanks to the <em>TNI</em> editor, my friend, <a href="https://twitter.com/GrecianFormula">Harry Kazianis</a>.  </p>
<div align="justify"> <a href="https://asiansecurityblog.wordpress.com/2014/11/07/my-national-interest-essay-on-the-ridiculous-media-hysteria-over-kim-jong-uns-disappearance/#more-3223" class="more-link">Continue reading <span class="meta-nav">&rarr;</span></a></div></p>
<div id="jp-post-flair" class="sharedaddy sd-rating-enabled sd-like-enabled sd-sharing-enabled"><div class="sharedaddy sd-sharing-enabled"><div class="robots-nocontent sd-block sd-social sd-social-icon-text sd-sharing"><h3 class="sd-title">Share this:</h3><div class="sd-content"><ul><li class="share-twitter"><a rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" data-shared="sharing-twitter-3223" class="share-twitter sd-button share-icon" href="https://asiansecurityblog.wordpress.com/2014/11/07/my-national-interest-essay-on-the-ridiculous-media-hysteria-over-kim-jong-uns-disappearance/?share=twitter" target="_blank" title="Click to share on Twitter"><span>Twitter</span></a></li><li class="share-facebook"><a rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" data-shared="sharing-facebook-3223" class="share-facebook sd-button share-icon" href="https://asiansecurityblog.wordpress.com/2014/11/07/my-national-interest-essay-on-the-ridiculous-media-hysteria-over-kim-jong-uns-disappearance/?share=facebook" target="_blank" title="Click to share on Facebook"><span>Facebook</span></a></li><li class="share-linkedin"><a rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" data-shared="sharing-linkedin-3223" class="share-linkedin sd-button share-icon" href="https://asiansecurityblog.wordpress.com/2014/11/07/my-national-interest-essay-on-the-ridiculous-media-hysteria-over-kim-jong-uns-disappearance/?share=linkedin" target="_blank" title="Click to share on LinkedIn"><span>LinkedIn</span></a></li><li class="share-reddit"><a rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" data-shared="" class="share-reddit sd-button share-icon" href="https://asiansecurityblog.wordpress.com/2014/11/07/my-national-interest-essay-on-the-ridiculous-media-hysteria-over-kim-jong-uns-disappearance/?share=reddit" target="_blank" title="Click to share on Reddit"><span>Reddit</span></a></li><li class="share-pinterest"><a rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" data-shared="sharing-pinterest-3223" class="share-pinterest sd-button share-icon" href="https://asiansecurityblog.wordp